         <div>
            <head>WHITE HOUSES</head>
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">Your door is shut against my tightened face,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">And I am sharp as steel with discontent;</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">But I possess the courage and the grace</l>
               <l enjamb="no">To bear my anger proudly and unbent.</l>
               <l enjamb="no">The pavement slabs burn loose beneath my feet,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">A chafing savage, down the decent street,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">And passion rends my vitals as I pass,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Where boldly shines your shuttered door of glass.</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Oh I must search for wisdom every hour,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Deep in my wrathful bosom sore and raw,</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">And find in it the superhuman power</l>
               <l enjamb="no">To hold me to the letter of your law!</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">Oh I must keep my heart inviolate</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Against the potent poison of your hate.</l>
            </lg>
            <byline>-Claude McKay</byline>
         </div>
      </body>
